<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-19T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-19T05:00:00-05:00" n="452" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5151/972: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-19T11:00:00+01:00">September
                                    19, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 19—9:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>893. For the Secretary of the Treasury from Cochran. Reference to my 892,
                            September 18, 10 p.m., Baumgartner telephoned me this morning that
                            Leith-Ross had also objected to inclusion of reference to eventual
                            return to gold standard and had indicated that certain revision in
                            phraseology would be necessary to suit British public. In final
                            interview before Leith-Ross’s departure for London Minister of Finance
                            Auriol stressed to him his insistence upon a simultaneous common
                            declaration.</p>
                        <p>It is arranged for me to communicate to Baumgartner tonight or tomorrow
                            morning any suggestions that may be received from you in the meantime.
                            [Cochran.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>